<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS SPICER AUTOMATE-2 - DISASSEMBLY - LOWER SHIFT TOWER</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="20">
        <title>LOWER SHIFT TOWER</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the wire harness (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302264">Figure 64</hotlnk>). Check the wires for cracks and breaks. Replace if
                necessary.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302264" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302264" filename="../figg13/g1302264.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 64. Wire Harness</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the four bolts and the actuator assembly shield (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302265">Figure 65</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302265" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302265" filename="../figg13/g1302265.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 65. Actuator Assembly Shield</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove four bolts and the actuator assembly from the lower tower (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302266">Figure 66</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302266" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302266" filename="../figg13/g1302266.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 66. Assembly From Lower Tower</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Keep the valve nut from turning as you loosen the air fitting nuts (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302267">Figure 67</hotlnk>). If you don't, you will accidentally disassemble the
                valves.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302267" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302267" filename="../figg13/g1302267.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 67. Loosen Air Fitting Nuts</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">The air fittings and lines can be removed as an assembly (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302268">Figure 68</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302268" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302268" filename="../figg13/g1302268.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 68. Remove Air Fittings &#38; Lines</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the valves. Note that they are marked "HI," "N" for neutral, and "LOW" (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302269">Figure 69</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302269" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302269" filename="../figg13/g1302269.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 69. Valve Removal</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the large and small O-ring from the bores of each valve (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302270">Figure 70</hotlnk>). Replace with new O-rings during reassembly.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302270" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302270" filename="../figg13/g1302270.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 70. Large &#38; Small O-Rings</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the hitch pin and the override plunger (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302271">Figure 71</hotlnk>). Remove and replace the three O-rings on the plunger and
                plunger cap.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302271" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302271" filename="../figg13/g1302271.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 71. Hitch Pin &#38; Override Plunger</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove both housing end caps and gaskets (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302272">Figure 72</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302272" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302272" filename="../figg13/g1302272.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 72. Housing End Caps</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a screwdriver to gently push against the shift rack and remove each piston (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302273">Figure 73</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302273" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302273" filename="../figg13/g1302273.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 73. Remove Each Piston</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Replace the two O-rings on each inner piston, and one O-ring on each outer piston (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302274">Figure 74</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302274" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302274" filename="../figg13/g1302274.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 74. Replace O-Rings</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the shift rack from the actuator housing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302275">Figure 75</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302275" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302275" filename="../figg13/g1302275.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 75. Shift Rack</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the four lower tower cover bolts (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302276">Figure 76</hotlnk>). Remove the cover.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302276" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302276" filename="../figg13/g1302276.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 76. Remove Cover</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the control arm, bolt and washer (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302277">Figure 77</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302277" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302277" filename="../figg13/g1302277.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 77. Control Arm, Bolt &#38; Washer</caption>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>Hold the shift shaft still as you remove the components. Holding the shaft will help prevent
                    damaging the control arm.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the automatic switch (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302278">Figure 78</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302278" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302278" filename="../figg13/g1302278.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 78. Automatic Switch</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Pull the shift shaft and shift fingers out of the housing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302279">Figure 79</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302279" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302279" filename="../figg13/g1302279.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 79. Shift Shaft &#38; Shift Fingers</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Replace the shift shaft O-ring with a new one (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302280">Figure 80</hotlnk>). Carefully use a screwdriver to lift the ring over the
                keyway to prevent cutting the ring.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302280" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302280" filename="../figg13/g1302280.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 80. Lifting O-Ring Over Keyway</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the snap ring to disassemble the shift fingers (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302281">Figure 81</hotlnk>). Inspect the shaft and key for wear or damage. If either
                needs to be replaced, replace them as a set.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302281" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302281" filename="../figg13/g1302281.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 81. Disassembled Shift Fingers</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the housing plugs (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302282">Figure 82</hotlnk>). Replace the O-rings.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302282" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302282" filename="../figg13/g1302282.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 82. Housing Plugs</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Push the shift pistons and joiner pin from the center of the housing out (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302283">Figure 83</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302283" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302283" filename="../figg13/g1302283.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 83. Shift Pistons &#38; Joiner Pin</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>Do not force both pistons out of the same side of the housing at the same time. Doing so might
                        bind the pistons.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <para>Replace the piston O-rings. Lower shift tower disassembly is complete.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
